The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a visit to a military facility in the Middle East. Pence expressed gratitude and admiration for the men and women serving in the 332nd Air Expeditionary Wing, also known as the Red Tails. He assured them that President Donald Trump supports and appreciates their efforts. Pence highlighted the accomplishments of the military in the fight against ISIS, stating that the terrorist organization has been crushed and its caliphate has fallen. He also mentioned the United States' determination to confront Iran's influence in the region and prevent it from acquiring a nuclear weapon. Pence addressed the government shutdown and promised to fight for military pay and benefits. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the strength and future of the United States, thanks to the dedication and sacrifice of its military personnel.